content: I thought this game was it, my next big time sink, but I can't keep a crew! I take it slow, stop at every spice bar along the way, and I still lose crew from just random stuff happening. For example: 1) Start new game on easy. 2) take 10 minutes customizing crew talents. 3) Take a mission (moral is high) and leave for target planet a short distance away. 4) Lose 5 crew after on arrival because a single random event happened on the way. 5) ???? What???? I want to play the game! Not try to hire and balance crew every few minutes. It's too bad, this game has potential. My advice to the developers, either balance events that cause crew moral to take a hit, or give the option to turn it off! Disappointed
This game is trash. I don't have no words or explanation but there isn't any real way to know how to get started
Buy once, enjoy forever. Mobile gaming needs to be more like this. Amazing game!

This is the closest game to Mount and Blade in terms of Management, Sandbox and Character Progression that I had put my hands on, EVER. At first I was relunctant as I always turn away on Turn-based RPG but this one hook me once I understand how things work. I just love how you can customize your ship, character and crew by your liking and roam around and do errands on different allied factions you come across to. I would recommend this to people who loves deep story telling + sandbox!
Amazing depth and intriguing gameplay. One of the best mobile games I've ever played, and I've played a lot of them. Highly recommend!
It's fun :)
I just love the game even though i am bad at it because there is so much to consider when starting a compaign but all in all great fun and storyline is awsome!!i recommend it highly!

By the flag this is an epic spacefaring sandbox game! Initially seems a little overwhelming but stick with it and you will be sucked into its vast glorious complexity. Varied missions, engrossing stories, near endless options to customise your officers, crew and ship. If turn based complex strategy is your thing you will not be disappointed and the regular updates give ever more options for build styles (love the new saboteurs). Download, enjoy and keep an eye on those scanners for Xenos...

One of the deepest and best mobile games you will ever play. It is a management Sim, Rogue-like RPG, with 4X feel and unlimited replayability. If you have never played a Trese Brothers game; this is a great one to start with. Join us in the Discord for help or to share your adventures. Continuous updates ensure more content is on the way!! As the game is closing up the 2.6 family of updates on the roadmap, TBG has proven, again; that they deliver on their promises. Cyber Knights sequel is next.

The Best $6.99 game on Google Playstore in my opinion. You play as a Captain - managing your crew, resources, and ship - as you traverse space and make a name for yourself. Kill, Trade, Hunt, Explore, or Smuggle for a living. Infinite replayability, dozens of Achievements (and rewards) to unlock and best of all - no paid in apps purchases or dlcs. Devs continually update the game making it even better. Discord community is awesome too if you need help. What are you waiting for? Buy it now!!
Just the best. An amazing full PC game that you can play on your phone because it is about substance not graphics

This is exactly what I'm looking for in a Space RPG game. I can't think of what else to say, just a few feedback that hopefully will get implemented in future updates: - I would like to have my saves synced across my devices (through google play account maybe?) - The ability to preview job's talents (inside the Job list). Currently it's not possible to see what talents are available before deciding Officers' 2nd and 3rd job, and I have to rely on my memory or some online guides.
Awesome both on PC and mobile
Great game with lots of replay value.

There are many people who will enjoy this game, right now I'm not one of them, I'd like the story to be a little more casual, and less lore intensive. However I'm happy to support the devs having played elite, they both seem to have a vision that I'd like to help them pursue!
Great game.

Holy space balls this game is hard! Well, hard by choice since you can customize the difficulty to suit your play style. There is a lot going on in the UI and that takes getting used to but the game provides tooltips/descriptions for pretty much everything, so that helps! Your crew WILL leave you, you WILL run out of money, but you WILL have fun while ruinong your space life!

Meh, first one was better. The first game you could take a little time and learn it and it was great in most ways. Now you have no choice but to look at the wiki because nothing is upfront and combat is downright a chore that is all but worthless. And if i play on a lower difficulty. No achievements for me Go get rip this game dont buy And look at the shiiity corporate level responses to 1 star reviews. I think ive read the same ones over a dozen times Yeah i think they MiSsEd tHe mArK with me
replyContent: Hey Rio, sorry Star Traders: Frontiers missed the mark for you. I am, at least, glad to hear that you enjoyed the original, Star Traders RPG from 2010. We'll keep working to improve and update Frontiers as long as we can. I'm also sad to hear that you felt my responses to reviews were too corporate. The company is just me and my brother. Best, Cory

content: I rarely give 5 stars. It truly deserves it. Developed are very active, still a lot of great updates, wiki is always up-to-date, they answer questions on steam, boards, reddit etc.
One of the best game ever, including PC games.
Everything you could want from a scifi rpg. Another solid Trese Bros title, thanks guys.

HOW MANY 89-90 MB UPDATES ARE WE GOING TO HAVE THIS YEAR LOL? ðŸ˜³ Update, here we go again. Listed as a 20mb update but when pressing to update it's the whole 195 mb resources , again, for the 20th time!

So much depth. Richness of a PC game. Great RPG turn-based strategy game set in a universe like a cross between Dune and Firefly, with a little Alien and the Expanse thrown in. Great replayability. And no microtransactions. Love these devs.
Great programmers, fun game

Paid for the full game just to have half the ships and classes locked behind some pointless achievments. No one wants to make a throw away save file to unlock an achievment. . .thats not fun. Thats not playing the game. Thats wasting everyones time on something no one enjoys and before you say "please check out forums if your not good enough to unlock it" thats not the point. Ive unlocked like half of them. And its sucked all the fun and joy out of the game to where i dont want to play anymore.
replyContent: Sorry to hear that you didn't have the experience we hoped for with the game. The unlock feature intends to reward players for exploring different play-styles with optional add-on content. Sad to hear that it was a miss for you. We will try to do better in the future.  --Cory

content: Fun,and challenging
Many random events and there are so many types of stats and attributes. It is an almost perfect rpg.
Best space trader rpg/sim on google play
No cloud save?
replyContent: No cloud save at this time, sorry. My brother and I are working on making it possible in the future.

content: This is my 1st Trese Bros game, & I'm an instant fan. Graphics aren't impressive, steep learning curve for combat, (expect your first couple characters to go down in flames.) It's a full on space opera with multiple story arcs & a mess of customization allowing you to pretty much make it your own story. This game takes some thought though. Best customer service I've seen in a game ever. No grind, no ads, no pay to win, nobody looting your resources when you put the game down to deal with RL.

Every thing I could look for in a space rpg and more. Runs fine on my Moto e5 play for reference of stability. Deducted a star because in game achievements reset on reinstall or transfer to new phone even though they are unlocked in the Google play record.
So far great, but no cloud save?
Loved your first game. This one is off the top though. Love the strategy and the customizability
Great game!

Decided to play this again after a while. It has moments of depth, but the whole vat-born honor guard quest ruins the early game. So out of balance and spoils the game's promise. Its impossible 99% of the time. I felt like throwing my phone across the room. To hell with this.
Always loved the star trader series, this one takes it to another level. One of the few mobile games that I enjoy playing for hours.
Scratches the sci-fi itch. Reminds me of the classic sci-fi games of the 90s

Normally I would really enjoy a game like this, but honestly the experience has only been frustrating. I don't see how simply flying your ship from one nearby planet to the next causes you to experience the plague, flesh-eating bacteria, 5 engine failures, 4 accidents, fires, explosions, etc etc causing you to lose 5 crew members when you land and paying more in repairs/healing/recruiting than you earned on your mission. Game would be more fun if it wasn't so unrealistically "hard"
replyContent: Sorry to hear that you are struggling with the game. We certainly have spent years tuning the difficulty curve and working on the challenges of balance within Star Traders but there is always room for improvement. Did you start playing on the lowest difficulty? We have a community of excited and experienced Captains waiting to help on Discord!

content: A lot of fun, very replayable, might take some time to learn game and background but in the end worth it. You can play it as easy or difficult as you like. So many ways to play and just as many ways to customize ships and crew. Oh... And the Xenos, fear the Xenos.
Top notch

I love this game and have played it, and the original star traders, for years. Controls are intuitive, artwork is well done, good storyline, and so on. So why is my rating 4 stars? One reason and, sadly, it's a biggie in my book. The game doesn't seem to save unlock progress. I got a new phone and, even after I logged into Google play, my previous unlock progress didn't seem to be saved. As such, I'm now stuck backtrack just to get some of my favorite content back. Good game, frustrating issue.
Updated accordingly...tumbs up

This game will suck away as many hours as you let it; it's perfect for the min/maxing number-cruncher, or for the flavorful role-player. Bugs are fixed really quickly, new content is added constantly, and the replayability is insane. On another note: do not be daunted by the numbers, or the sheer amount of content. Remember, there's no shame in restarting a run, or in asking the internet for help! Shalun guide you, Captains ðŸ˜Ž
replyContent: Thank you so much for the review, Luke. Positive feedback from happy Captains make it all worth it. I look forward to delivering another hundred updates. ðŸ™‚

content: I have no regrets in buying this game. It is all worth it. The game is spectacular.
I hate this game. Permadeath on hard... but It is much fun, very challenging and deep. Recomend 100%

I have played the OG Star Traders shortly after it initially launched and been playing the Elite version from time to time for the past couple of years. The sequel is better on (nearly) all fronts, especially graphics and UI. Expanded gameplay, with fleshed out narrative and squad combat/risk cards added make it an instant classic for anyone into tactical RPG/exploration games. Hopefully more ships and rewards are added to mirror plethora of options in ST1 - apart from that, absolute must have
Survival space RPG,

I know many people like these games. And think the trese Brothers are some kind of saviors of the android market, and that they make games with more heart than many others. Or that the trese bros can do no wrong. Well I'm hear to tell you something a bit different. It's better than they say. I love these dudes games. I come back to each of them randomly and I hope they remake cyber knight in this quality. Props guys. You deserve all your praise.

Absolute favourite game. So much deeper than I expected, and still being updated! I mostly play on PC but had to buy it for my phone as well to scratch the itch on the go, and also to support the devs with some more money. Also immediately backed their next project, Cyber Knight, on kickstarter. The only criticism I have is that I wish that the passage of time during variuos tasks was emphasized a bit better.

Very poor interface for a mobile game. Essentially unplayable for any type of cellular phone, although it seems like it could be a great game if played on a computer, and perhaps an OK game if played on a tablet.
replyContent: While the game is pretty popular with phone players, we are always looking to improve the experience for our users, and really appreciate the feedback! If there is anything specific we can look into, please contact us at cory.trese@gmail.com. Good luck, Captain!

content: I bought this game with very low expectations. Purely because I liked the idea behind it and I thought it might scratch the "elite" itch I had. Not only did it surpass everything I thought it might be, but I continue to come back to it as one of the few games I can immerse myself into. The only other games I've gotten this feeling from are heavily modded bethesda games. The devs have also continued updating the game over the years with fairly significant free updates. Well worth the price.
replyContent: Happy to hear that you enjoyed the game. If there is anything we can do for you, just let us know at cory.trese@gmail.com

content: Somewhere along the way an update utterly destroyed this game. Every new game I start I am constantly having crewmembers desert the ship without warning. I've had mutinies after leaving worlds with full pay, full health, and everyone gone to the spice hall. Then there are the times I actually get low morale warnings and it takes three planets worth of spice halls to cover everyone. This is on Normal difficulty, mind. Devs, fix this.
replyContent:
Sorry to hear that you are having problems with Crew management. I doubt the cause was one of the updates. We monitor analytics for Crew behavior with every release to ensure that this type of bug wouldn't last long if it existed.

Happy to try to help on Discord or over email at cory.trese@gmail.com

content: Very fun game, wide open. Tons of hours of playtime available. Can seem overwhelming at first but once you learn the game and find your groove in one of the many playstyles, it's great

I own 250+ ps4 games, and i spend most of my free time playing this game on my phone and on steam. Awesome gameplay mechanics, great story, very immersive, and extremely replayable. If you're looking for a strategic space sim rpg/roguelike, you found the right game. I recommend playing with permadeath once you get the hang of things. Wouldn't recommend to those seeking a fast paced action experience
replyContent: Thanks so much for the review. We feel like it can be "fast paced action experience" if you tap fast enough. <3

content: Best game ever, and the updates keep coming. Outstanding work!
replyContent: Glad you're enjoying the game on the S8. If there is anything we can do to help, just let me know at cory.trese@gmail.com Have a wonderful day!

content: The worldbuilding in this game is essentially a vision of Frank Herbert's Dune. Loved the overall concept and remarkable depth of the game, but it did get repetitive after a while. However, the ability to customize the mode of gameplay does offer a large variety of options in terms of replayability.
An incredible reimagining of the first Star Traders. It's polished, intricate, and very replayable.
Been playing the original on and off since launch, this is even better. Great value, awesome game. Got a 40k-esque Grimdark feel to it to top it off ;)

Great stadegy game. It has loads of things to do. Micro-manage to ship resources, personnel, battles, etc. Sometimes it seems you are doing the same thing over and over but you can change careers, buy permits, explore space and planets. Overall it's an awesome downtime game. You must be interested in this style or you will not like it long time. Finally a great buy without in-game purchases and time to upgrade games (There's none of it.) Great job and thanks!

No matter what difficulty I play on the computer always wins I'm always pitted against ships and crews that are far in advance of mine or simply run out of money and not able to do anything and I have to abandon accounts and delete them and start the whole game over which is not fun

My favorite old school rpg for the last two years. I have bought the game both here and steam . My only wish for this game is to have a way to transfer my save between platforms or ability of cloud saving. Keep up the good. This is how a true rpg game should be.

Great game ,good mechanics, fun variety of missions, incredible depth a must for any space exploration rpg game lovers. My only small complaint would be the lack of background art for combats whether your boarding a vessel , fighting pirates while exploring a planet or even facing police in an alleyway near a black market its always the same corridor like background , it brakes the immersion a bit , an art pack upgrade add on would be a good update. Still its awesome.

Extraordinary. I loved Cyber Knights, but the Brothers have really outdone themselves this time! Amazingly deep, without losing a drop of the incredible attention to detail that makes Trese Brothers stand out. A masterpiece, and one of the first games I've ever spent money on. NO REGRETS!

Great value for the quality. You can only superficially change the actual world in terms of faction interaction. Thats one thing I wish were better. The game is quite fun otherwise. Ive been being an addict with the Serenity soundtrack in the background.

Been playing trese brothers games for a while now... Like before 2015 kinda while now... And the amount of progress these two brothers have made, on star traders frontier alone, is just amazing. I value the Trese Brothers because they're level of work reminds me of the days when consoles were new concepts, and the games that came out had content. Now it's about graphics, the bros kept it old school
One of the best rpg space games. Options galore. High space adventure. All the systems and intricacies you could want.
Been playing the Trese Bros. games for a long time. They always deliver quality and support. This game is no exception.

Truth is I really enjoyed and still am enjoying this game. It gives freedom of choice to the players that most others don't. content: Love it.
Very enjoyable.
I LOVE IT! Great job Trese brothers. Captures that old school RPG game feeling.

There's a lot to like about star traders, but it is a poorly designed game. There are twice as many mechanics than there need to be. There are two times the number of factions that you can keep track of across two times the number of planets that you can keep track of. The engines are there to make a good game with interesting decisions, but only if the game is scaled back to the point where your decisions have a real impact.
replyContent: Sorry to hear the game was a miss for you. We will keep working to improve. Feel free to email me at cory.trese@gmail.com or join our Discord if you'd like help with the mechanics. Thanks!

Trese brothers have done it again. Been a fan of these devs for many years as they've always made some of the coolest indie games on mobile. This is no exception, an outstanding game with a deceptive amount of complexity and depth.
Kinda boring

Love this game, it reminds me of Escape Velocity: Nova. It's a bit of a steep learning curve, so start on basic. Love the sandbox in space idea. It would be great if there were more things happening in the universe. More random events and opportunities to receive ship upgrades as quest rewards.
If the first one had you hooked...this one will keep you on a journey for hours on end. Completely worth the price and the devs are awesome.
good game, long hours of entertainment, hope they will make a sequel, with more ship designs

Not bad. Definitely a fun game. Well worth the money. (edit) After playing this game for a few months I've decided that it deserves 5 stars. This is one of the best games I've ever played and I've devoted many many life hours to conquering its universe. Thanks for this masterpiece!

This game is excellent. No micro transactions. No ads. Clearly game design focused on fun and not profit. A breath of fresh air in the current mobile game culture. More games should take note of its design.

Easily worth the price. The lore book alone is a fantastic bit of scifi reading, but add in the dev accessibility (active on reddit and elsewhere), no ads, a true sandbox 4X experience... this game sets a benchmark for other games to strive for.

The game has a lot of depth, story and ways to have fun. If I were to suggest something for the future, possibly another class that can focus on healing crew in crew battles, and a ship you can start with that has 1 ship hanger preinstalled. Otherwise, keep the content rolling!
Love this game. So many possibilities during the game. Game play is also qood. Hope they could create more games like this and keep updating!

This is a great game. I appreciate the work that went into every aspect of it, from the branching storyline to the art to the way you can take any part of it and make it your own (like you can become a trader or a bounty hunter, or an explorer to a smuggler, etc...) just like you can in the very best sandbox games. It's just a joy to play and the hours just disappear. It is just my favorite game for the moment.

A perfect game for mobile devices as the turn based system allows for pausing at any time. No multi-player, no ads, a good callback to "old school gaming". I'll most likely buy this on multiple platforms. Easy enough to start, but very deep when a player gets more involved. Online guides could use a better format, as most of the information is community driven, but lots of times the fun is experimenting and figuring out what works best for yourself.
Great game.
So far very good!
Like the game so far. And I realize I haven't even scratched the service just barely starting. I will prefer a more of a 3-D top down version but that's just me and I'm sure as just a Matter of time.
One of the best games i have ever played. Keep up the good work devs!

This is one of the best science fiction games to be found on Android. There's a (somewhat) branching storyline, plenty of missions to complete and a smartly designed interface. The constant stream of updates and tweaks shows commitment like few other devs. Pick it up now!
I love the constant updates. Will support this developer more by buying their other games. Thanks to Kickstarter backers for bringing us more content for version 3.0.87!
Fantastic. I backed this game and was not disappointed.

One of the best games on the app store. I've been playing off and on for a while. Really fun exploring and getting into trouble. Difficulty kinda spikes when the aliens show up. Even on easy, I'd be rolling over the human enemies and getting owned by the aliens. I still dread running into them, but having some tough enemies isn't bad. It's been a while since this game came out, but as of this writing the devs are still updating it. Also, no IAPs or ads, just buy the game and play. That's rare.
One of the best purchases i made ever. This Game offers so much content and is still updated with even More Features. Advice: buy :)
Immersive, beautiful, and endless growth! Is there a way to sync mobile version & steam save slots?
I like the desktop version better but I still own this one. Offline, incredibly deep, complex, long game. Can't recommend highly enough

100's of hours sank into both mobild and PC! This developer has me in their grasp!!!

the game is awsome but the character image wont load in and the plants will giltch and not load in but overall the game is amazig.

I've been playing this game on PC and it's amazing and one of the best games I've ever played, a masterpiece. Surprisingly complex and full of contents, with the release of mobile version you can play it on the go. Keep up the great work!
Bought and was about to download until the asked for access to my media files and photos and all that and i said no thank you I'll have a refund instead. Eff these people.
replyContent: We are very sorry for the confusion. The permission is required to download the game files from Google Play. That's how Google Play IAB downloads work because on Google Play the APK download size cannot be greater than 100M. The game doesn't access your files, just needs a place to store the downloaded media (sound, graphics) files.

content: Fantastic game, well worth the money! If you haven't tried it yet, you're missing out. Only problem I had with it was the outright lie told really early on that indicates you can influence the outcome of an event, but you actually can't. Other than that, great game

There are a lot of ways to incrementally improve but at the end of the day that's all you do. You've experienced all the gameplay there is after the first battle; the flow of battle, the strategy, nothing changes. It's a mindless grind for incremental improvements to stay ahead of the enemy.
This game has more updates and support than most AAA titles. I appreciate the developers. Great scifi game to get lost in
Its fantastic, huge game, tons of replayability, easy controls. Havent found any bugs. It's a great game

WOW! DAMN! BUY IT NOW! This game is good, this is the best RPG the PLAYSTORE currently has to offer without a doubt. This is a must play - highly addictive. Do you like RPG's? Can you afford this game? Then buy it NOW! You will not be disappointed (unless you are an RPG n00b and/or illiterate) Spoiler: This game is not for whimps or whiners. Excellent overall gameplay with tons of replay value (does it even end though?). Sandbox space opera reminiscent of Infinite Space by SEGA for Nintendo DS.
LoFi space adventure.
Best sci fi phone RPG by far by pepe get it

Very polished game. Regularly updated and patched. Does not have fanciful graphics but more than makes up with gameplay. Steep learning curve due to various options (ship design, skills, attributes etc) and paths on gameplay.
Dope, like heroin
Got this in gem in both my PC and android!

What a fantastic game for a small one off fee. You have everything you needs for weeks if not months of unadulterated fun. You trade, you fight, you spy, you steal & if all that fails you smooth talk your way out of TROUBLE & Believe trouble will fined you. So be prepared or Die.

Awesome! Overwhelming at first, But learning everything is fun. Besides solid game mechanics, the Universe feels dynamic and alive thanks to very good dialogue writing and chatacter background. content: Great game ! There are so many games of exploration, combat, etc, and yet so few of them have a story at all, much less an interesting one, and deep world building. It is a shame. No matter how good the gameplay is, if the story is bland or even absent, and if the world is uninteresting, then I will lose interest very quickly. It seems that 95% of the games I try are like that. It is so rare for me to find a game I really enjoy playing, such as this one.
This is my favorite game on Android. The Trese Brothers are the high standard that everyone else on the Play store should be measured by. Thank you and Keep up the good work.
Amazing! Absolutely Amazing!! And to think I didn't used to imagine their last game could ever be topped!?!

I was loving this game and got very far into my current playthrough.. before i let my money dip too low. Now I'm screwed. I can't buy fuel, can't raise morale. The fact that you can't bounce back from having no money is absurd. I can't sell modules? I have so much illegal cargo because that's all pirates drop but I can't sell it even though I've spent money on raising trade permits? If you are going to make such a punishing game mechanic then AT LEAST make it apparent to the player. I quit.
replyContent: Digging out of debt can be accomplished several ways. Patrol, explore, harvest fuel, etc. Sorry to hear that you had a negative experience with the game. Hopefully you give it another try sometime. Good luck! Email me at cory.trese@gmail.com if you need anything.

Star Traders: Frontiers is a massive, complex and extremely difficult version of Drug Wars in space. Basically, you go from planet to planet to planet trying to buy low and sell high. All the while you to contend with random death and a story so convoluted I lost track of which mission was for who like 2 hours in. When traveling between planets it's not uncommon to fight 2 or 3 powerful ships, any one of which can kill you. I think this game has potential but as it is, it's almost unplayable.
Problem fix. Thanks.

I've played Cyber Knights and loved it for its intricate, yet accessible systems, its writing and its artwork. All of those have become even better over the years and Frontiers is the result of that. What I love most about the Trese Brothers is how they GET me. They know I want to find things out for myself, but sometimes need a bit of explanation. They understand that I like delving into the flavour text, but sometimes just want to plough through. But most of all, they know what a good RPG is.

General Verdict: Very good game. Pros: - Fairly steep learning curve, which I like because it keeps you engaged and challenged and provides rewarding breakthrough moments when you master a new aspect of the game. - Many different play styles and specialization paths. Cons: - Weak, repetitive end game. Once you have configured your ship and crew to a point where traveling space is relatively safe and your revenue stream is strong, there isn't anything else to do but hording wealth.

Procedural galaxy, dynamic economy, lots of activity types, boarding, a hand-crafted campaign with character development and, somehow, good dialogue! Add cloud saves and I'd buy it on PC too.

This game has a lot to offer. It's like a chilled out version of Elite with a surprising amount of story to be found out there in the stars. I find myself having the most fun racing against time to accomplish missions trying to keep my standing clean with all the factions as best I can. The reason this is fun for me is that satisfying all the factions is nigh on impossible. The reputation system almost entirely depends on gaining favor with one faction by harming another faction. The original star traders game was actually excellent in this regard, but this spiritual successor ramps up this aspect of the game by a lot. Most importantly in this regard, the game gives you unfolding narratives to follow that will influence the standing you have with the factions, and that to me is the real coup de gras here. The game rewards you to make the game harder on yourself once you finish all the story missions at the beginning of it should you choose to continue with what the game had to offer in the previous iteration, and best yet, within the narrative of these story missions the game tells you "Hey. You don't have to participate in this. If you do it will impact your reputation a bunch when you start operating without the framework of these story missions"

And I've only barely scratched the surface on what can be done here.

At first I was really excited about this and it looks very deep and detailed. However I've put a fair amount of time into this and now it just feels a bit repetitive and kind of pointless. Personally I'd prefer a clear target and a way to "finish" the game (although I know I'm probably not in the majority of players with that view). I am level 34 now and I don't see much point in playing on. Is this worth $11? Absolutely. Is this something I'll be playing 6 months after I buy it? Honestly no.
Too good for mobile ðŸ˜‚ðŸ‘
ðŸ‘ðŸ˜Ž

This scratches the open-world spacefaring itch like no game has since Freelancer. Incredibly deep and rich in both strategic options and story possibilities, but (especially on the lowest difficulty settings) forgiving enough that a newbie can learn the ropes. Bravo to the Trese Brothers, and may they only keep getting better.
Another fine game from Trese brothers. Their trademark care and attention to detail really shines through. This is a multi-layered adventure experience that can go quite deep with the gameplay.

I love the community around the game money well spent I am also happy with the engagement of the devs on the discord too. Overall the game is worth getting and you choose how you play a true rpg and one that will last.

Man I'm addicted to your style. This is another game to dive into if you love figuring out an insane asylums amount of mechanism working against you. Also the amount customization makes this replayable af.
Just wish I could cross save over different devices and PC. Other than that this game is brilliant!
replyContent: Thanks for the feedback and review. With a team of only two people, we are doing the best we can. The saves are compatible between all builds and many players move saves with the cloud. We, unfortunately, don't have a better solution at this time. We will work to improve for future titles.

content: Obviously it has potential, but in all honesty the text is too small to enjoy on a mobile screen, probably better suited for a tablet or PC, shame, I'll have to pass
How about cloud save. I have a tablet and a phone, which I want to play on the tablet at nights and on phone during daytime, of course with a single save file.
Took me a minute to get the hang of it, but it was well worth the effort. Congrats to the devs, this is a superb mobile game.

I've got all of their games, and I love them. Not even the weird crash when looking at the crew section is enough to warrant a less than 5 star rating from me. It's not really an issue, I know my phone isn't the best. I'd absolutely definitely 100% recommend this game, and I'm going to buy whatever they make next. Love you guys, you're awesome!

Imagine..Space. The Final Frontier. You? A..err Pirate? Diplomat? Jack-of-all-trades good-for-nothing? All for what? Your Faction? Your crew family? Glory? Money? An Ideology? Xenophobia? Well..whatever YOU desire. Freedom..of Choices. THAT will be The Premise of this Masterpiece. Jump in blind. Die a lot. (Hey, the future has clone-tech, no?) Use Your Imagination. Be Alive. Feel it. Experience it. For the price of a meal? Constant updates and top-notch service. My Word. Guaranteed Satisfaction.
An offline single player mobile game rhat's actually good? It's miraculously good. Updated regularly with expanded content. You won't regret buying this one.
Another Smash Hit From These Very Talented Brothers. This Game Has Everything And Satisfies My Dreams Of Being In Another World.--Thank YouðŸ˜Š
Incredible. Exceptionally good.
Amazing. These devs have always done great work!
If you make more games like this id continue to buy them, Id also pay for good content dlc
The game was too dull. Sort of interesting but not enough. There was pretty much no point in upgrading ships either do to the negative big ships get.
replyContent: Appreciate for the feedback. I am sad to hear that you had a bad experience with the game. We will keep working to improve for the players who are exploring the depths of the game. Sorry you couldn't get into it. Feel free to email at cory.trese@gmail.com.    thanks!!!

content: Not enough too do still fun though
Trese Brothers does it again. One of the best roleplay sims available in store. You will play and replay this game forever.

If you like the style of a text based RPG mixed with some side scroll graphics this is a great game. It reminds me of some of the older games for PC when PC gaming was still young. I appreciate the nostalgic feel and the depth that went into the story.
Trese Brothers, you have done it again. I've been a loyal fan since the original Star Traders, and this game definitely showcases how far you've come. Thanks for all your hard work, guys!
Love the game, loved the first one, only thing I don't fully like is not being able to buy blank ships that you can design your self
Great game
Just awesome, awesome

Hands down, the best devs & most replayable game on mobile. Continually adding content - and not just the storyline, but to all aspects of this sandbox (you can have as much or as little involvement in the story as you'd like, but your decisions will matter.)
quality game.
Love this game

One of the best games I've ever played ! With depth and an interesting storyline that you can make choices and the outcome changes or isn't the same entirely each play through ! The game mechanics are amazing . So much potential with this game enjoying the new updates :) Hope to see even more content as time goes on. Great job Devs

One of the relatively few mobile games without ads, that is an actual game, not a skinner box slot machine, and a very good game at that. Nit just good for mobile either - properly good. It's a deep sim in an accessible package. Mobile port has some UI issues still, but nothing major.
One of the best games on mobile. Lots of content, variety of different playstyles, no IAPs. Definitely worth the money.
Just a great game in general, in depth and regular updates.
Great game, very detailed

This is a really good game, the first from the Trese Brothers I've really gotten into seriously. This game shines in its mechanics: trading, crew management, traveling, ship and crew combat are all very polished. My only gripe is that I've found smaller ship builds a lot more feasible than big ship builds. The big ship builds do reward you by letting you have enough crew to have the skills to be great at everything, but they aren't necessarily better at any one task.

Amazing game with lots of depth. And NO MICRO TRANSACTIONS. If you like science fiction and a space adventure games this is a really fun experience, with a somewhat decent story, exploration and combat mechanics. It does throw you into the deep end at first, but once you understand how things work it gets very addictive.

More like 3.5 stars. I'm a space game geek. Therefore I'm bias. I like how the game follows a certain story line that is interesting and to a certain extent adheres to my earlier decisions. The controls are simple and obvious, though there is no tutorial for them, I don't need them anyways. However, this game feels very repetitive. Especially when there are missions that need me to jump 14 times, I would need to retreat from at least 14 encounters.

best ever buuut. Sep 19 update. needs more ships espcecialy high end ships. i love the chracter skills and lvl ups. really tho we need more upgrades for ships and more clan specific up grades, finally we need more places to unload xeno relics.Story missions need more and they need to be spead over time line more. All crew should be able to use specality gear or at least wingmen please. Still the best space trader game ever love every moment of it!
Impressive as always.
There is no stopping the dream team. Maybe one day they'll share their secrets about how 2 brothers can do so much.

The Brothers Trese have made a great game even better. This is an entertaining and exciting experience. I love the ability to choose from a storyline or sandbox play through. The modifications to ships are so much more in depth and impactful, the playable characters have personal traits and development which seriously impacts so many aspects. It offers replay ability that is seldom found in recent games. I hope to one day see the enigmatic Trese bros adapt this epic to a fantasy seafaring game.
What a gem If you're looking for a space sandbox RPGs, look no further
Just another gimmick google game that milks you for your time, not skill.
replyContent: I am sorry to hear you had a poor experience with the Android port of our title. If you have any questions or concerns please feel free to contact me at cory.trese@gmail.com

content: It pains me a lot to review this game. There's clearly lots of love and passion put into it by its developers. This is clearly the type of an actually complex game that is incredibly hard to come by on mobile. However, unfortunately I can't say that I like to play it. Why? Because the core gameplay loop itself (fighting on ships or with crew) is on itself pretty shallow even though it's covered by layers and layers of fluff on top. I wish combat allowed more options and strategy instead.
replyContent: I am sad to hear you disliked our game so much. We spent several years focusing on adding depth to the core gameplay loops and it is disappointing to hear that we failed you. Perhaps our next game will be more your style!

content: Incredibly in-depth sandbox adventure game, with compelling choices, and a real-time changing world. The learning curve is very much worth it. Awesome game. Best money I've spent on any game. 4 Months later: This game is frequently updated and has very high replay value.
Cool and Complex!

Complicated Rogue Space RPG I love you can be any type captain, many templates . I laughed for those who cant get the game. MY Captain Merchant/Commando / Diplomat on impossible mode, yes the hardest mode in game. A pacifist build with no locker or ship weapons. I may not completely beat all stories mission , I draw no weapons , no crew combat. I still dominate the galaxy's with politics,. Soon to share my pacifist build on impossible and working on my next ship pacifist ship.

Deep, polished, stat-y, and fun. The Trese Brothers truly care about the games they produce and this shows every step of the way in Star Traders: Frontiers. There is great replayability because there are many ways to play this game and do well. I have often found myself choosing to play this game rather than going on my PC. 100% worth the buy, and I recommend to anyone who loves RPGs and/or sci-fi.

This is 1 of my fav 25 games of all time. Bgt their other 1st rogue rpg game many years ago. Was fantastic. Now with this one supported again. Done passionately with understanding of true rpg gamers wanted. Deep in depth. Character n ship customizations. Freedom to roam tons of ships. Reasonable price for such a true rpg game to play at Yr own time at Yr own pace no rat life chase game. 5 stars truly worth it. Keep up the great work trese.

Thank you, Trese Brothers for another fun mobile game. No in app purchases, no adds, just hours of fun for a cheap price. Wish more companies were not so greedy and made games like you. Looking forward to your next game, keep doing great work
Love this game. Have it for steam but I've clocked way more hours on Android version. The continued support is great. There has been a steady stream of content since I started playing.
LOVE it

best mobile game I have ever played, I cannot believe this game was made by 2 people, ever since I played Templar battleforce I have bought every game these guys make, we have to support independent developers like these 2 who can design a game without a major publisher/studio telling what to include and not include, this game has everything and the depth is amazing, I just wish you guys would add some of the bonus content that's listed as coming soon for the achievements, still tho best game.

Unfortunately it crashes for me with is sad since Gplay said it was compatible with my device, this said, I have the game on my Pc and it's amazing. It's a vast universe that is very rich in lore and the playthrough possibilities are extremely numerous. There is no game that let's you manage that many aspects of a starship and it's crew. I will gladly give this Dev team my money even if my device is not compatible, I'll have a great game waiting when I upgrade my device.

What a lovely space cowboy RPG. The story is fun and the game is engrossing. If you're on the fence about buying this game, consider this:. 1. There are no evil in app purchases; 2. You're supporting legit indie development. Thanks devs. I appreciate you.

Pretty hard at first but once you've explored and get used to the game it becomes simple and fun, it gives you a lot of freedom to do what you want you are not forced to follow the story line and you decide what type of missions you want to do
Was in the kickstarter from the very beginning. I played enough trese bros games to trust them with my money. They have always delivered more than they promise. Top notch!
Best devs. This game is worth every penny.
Played the original and enjoyed it, this is great on PC and excellent on Android. A game of such depth on mobile is a rare treat. Can't go wrong with a Trese Bros. game!

this game is a complete joke all it does is punishes you at every turn without you being able to counter, before you say you can do this and do that... let me ask you with high level dr and the best medical bay how long does it take to heal 3 crew members? the answer: until you find a port that is capable of doing that the chance of finding a port is 4% (80% are hostile and 80% can't heal) if you wait for your dr you will wait indefinitely because your dr is useless, poor balance and poor game
replyContent: I am sorry to hear that you had a bad time with the game and difficulty. We have spent a lot of time working on this game and I am sad we missed the mark for you. One thing that always gets positive reviews are the numerous and flexible difficulty settings. Start on Basic if struggling. Thanks!!!

content: A really addictive game. It has fun mechanics, an interesting storyline, and some nice world building. It's a bit overwhelming at first because it drops you in the game with very little instructions, but once you explore, try things here and there, you'll eventually understand the gameplay flow and see how addictive it can be. One of the most satisfying purchases I've ever made on the Play Store. It does have some small technical issues, but nothing too troublesome.

The game is hard but long and fun! There is a lot of customization and while sometimes it seems like there's a lot to do, give it a shot. Read the online documentation because this is a full desktop game and there is a lot to learn. This is not some cut down game with mobile users in mind, so expect there to be a lot of complexity as you would expect that a full desktop game would have.

excellent gameplay BUT most unlocks only in (very) hard game mode, no cloud sync and save folder only accessible on rooted devices. so when my device crashes all progress is lost. bad design decisions :-(.
replyContent: Sorry to hear you had a negative experience with the game. Most players like the unlock system, I am sad you didn't enjoy them. We will keep this in mind for future games where hopefully we won't have to make such difficult budget decisions!

content: A lot of depth here, very good overall.

The android port of this game is not recommended right now. This is the only version of the game that you will be unable to back up and recover your save game unless you have rooted your phone. If you delete the app, you have to start over. If you change or upgrade your phone, game saves are gone. There is no saving to the cloud. For a game of this depth where you can have a game going for months to lose it all makes it not worth investing time in. Hope to see the Trese Bro's release a fix.
Best Trese Brothers game yet. The learning curve is massive but once you get used to it it's an awesome game with a bunch of replay value.

Easily my favorite game of all time on the play store. Really solid space rpg with turn based combat(both ship and person). Lots of ship choices and customization, a cool crew system, and tons of quests to do in a pretty decently sized galaxy. Lots of factions to choose from and ways to play from a simple merchant all the way to a loyalist bounty hunter. Definitely give it a shot if you want a good scifi mobile rpg that's updated constantly.

This has been an addicting game! I play it during slower times at work and the gameplay is repetitive, but engaging. It is the first game that moves the interesting story along whether you choise to take part or not. You have a lot of freedom of choice, and Id love to see even more content added! Thanks Star Traders team for making a great game!!!

I want to love everything about this game, just like all the Trese games. And I did, until my phone died. That's when I found there's 0 backup support. This might be OK if all content was immediately available. But you have to spend weeks / months to earn lots of in-game content with achievement unlocks. If you upgrade / break your phone, oh well. I love this game. What I hate is: losing all my work, with no ability to re-access locked content that Play Games Achievements can track just fine.
replyContent: Sorry to hear that you hated the game so much. Both of the two people who work on it will try to be better in the future. Thanks!!!

content: Buy now! I have this on both my laptop and my android and I would of paid double for the value and fun that I've gained from playing.

AMAZING!! so look graphically this isn't the best game on mobile, but that's not what they were going for it has an art style that it sticks to. the depth of the RPG mechanics in this game is the most I've seen in a mobile game. There is a learning curve to the game for sure but its not darksouls. not to mention that every time I open the app store I get an update and they're constantly improving the game play and RPG mechanics.
Amazingly deep and engaging

This game is really awesome. It has absurd amount of depth to be on Android which is the reason I bought it. Controls and optimisation is also pretty nice. It is not draining my battery, which is also awesome. Now to buy other games of these genius brothers...

It exceeded my expectations, the depth to the game is great, other mobile games dont compare in terms of quality. Theres many jobs and roles to fulfill, alot of quests and content to complete. With an interesting faction system and good questlines, you've cooked up something good. The replayability is high, theres consistent updates with free additional content and bug fixes, and NO IAPs. Worth every penny Ive spent, looking forward to your next projects.
Has a bit of a learning curve but it's pretty fun with lots of depth. It has lots of good resources for information on game systems, but most everything can be figured out by playing.
STF is an amazing game. It may not be to everyone's taste, but if a sandbox RPG with lots to learn and a thousand different things to do appeals, you should really give it a look.

Enjoying so far! Great game, but could've been AWESOME. May I suggest: - few more ships - a "working" ship build (e.g. shield focused, damage dealer, explorer / long voyages, carrier type, etc.) - artifacts (mined, developed/researched, acquired from random encounters) - multiplayer (with trading, coop / pvp play) *will suggest more as I play. Only been playing for a couple of days, and instead of playing STO, I now play this. btw, thanks for constantly updating the game. its getting more fun.
Good game

Fantastic game and galactic sim. Follow the story, or just set out on your own to see the universe. Despite this being an expansive game world, TB keeps adding more (free!) content. Keep up the good work, Cory and Andrew!

This game has the familiar trader/pirate/bounty hunter triangle that you would expect. Ship to ship combat is turn based and requires you to manage your range and buff/debuffs to win with optional ship boarding gameplay. Crew combat seems inspired by Darkest Dungeon and feels rewarding. There are a lot of different ways to make credits in the void and they all feel unique and challenging enough to make your choices matter. I wish I had more space here to praise this game and it's devs. BUYNOW
Really scratches that space sim itch.
Rapid dev for frequent quality updates to content. No microtransactions. Worth your $.

Addictive, cool time sink (great open world with cool story quest lines. Would be nice if there's an actual play time displayed (like in steam, I'm about 400+hours there already) so I'd know how much of my life was wasted playing this version as well :)

Amazing game with complex and in depth mechanics, the type of game that you can sink hours into and still be wanting more! There's a great story that's well thought out and implemented but with everything else with Star Traders Frontiers you can choose to jump into the story, do some of the never ending quests available or create the character you want and do what you like! EDIT: The constant roll out of updates is really amazing and the updates are big content updates at that!! 5 STARS all day!
Gets repetitive and tedious after a couple of days
Thus game js so fun and immersive. Ive been playing for over a year still literally my favorite mobile game!

I love all Tresebrother games, but this one wasn't as good as the orginal, i like the idea of a blackhole but you have made too many and too many small maps, i would rather few warp gates which costs more to use and bigger maps, anyways unfortunately this wasnt for me

I'm a Treese fan for life, I've never been disappointed with one of their games. Great game content, but the UI is kind of bloated and the text is really cramped. Turn-based and heavy on reading, this is not a game for everyone -- if you want to try something a little smarter than a lot of other space sims, you might want to try it out!
Such a vast game. With useful auto select features to help speed it up. I'd also just mention that you can speed up the slower animations in the options once you get into the game

Graphics and gameplay like a mobile game, plot and reputation systems like a 4X. Feels like they made things too complex for such a simplist style. Played for a couple hours and suddenly couldn't find any missions to do and had no idea what i should do. I bet this game has tons of stuff to do but its locked behind i dont know what and didn't give me enough reason to find out.
a great game that is constantly updated for free. this is the height of mobile games and I've even thought about getting it on steam too as it is one of the best space sandboxes ever.
Can't read the lore book, not beginner friendly.
This game has a relatively high learning curve. However, after figuring out the game, it is a very enjoyable premium full game!
Awesome game!

Good overall but some parts play very slowly and impact the overall fun. Especially if you set yourself up for boarding combat ship combats can take longer and longer as you have to grind through multiple rounds of grunts. A rebalance that makes enemy officers / captain tougher but appear faster or more often could solve this issue, it seems to me.
awesome rpg... great dev.
I appreciate the fairly quick response. I'm still having trouble getting the game to start. I've sent more details and screenshots via gmail and hope to hear back. Thank you.
replyContent: Sorry to hear you're having this issue. We're happy to help if you can send more details to cory.trese@gmail.com.  Including a screenshot would also help!

content: constantly closes and kicks me out ..& no response
love it

This feels like Oregon Trail in space, and I love it. One big thing I wish they had was slightly more interaction with the ship itself, such as actually going into the different rooms of the ship when checking on shipmates and having character building dialogue on board.
Exceptional. A true masterpiece.
Exceptional space opera game
This game is too complicated to play on your phone. Way too complicated.

"Depart" not an option after sucessfully demanding tribute, only fight or retreat, that doesn't even make sense. 75% of the time press and hold doesn't bring up the planet info box without trying multiple times while messing with planet positioning on screen and zoom level. No tutorial, it's like dumping you into civ5 with no basic tutorial or advisor.
awesome game!
not worth 6.99
great game and the owners are responsive, money well spent. Let me add something more, this is gona be a classic one day.ðŸŒ¹
A very well executed space intrigue sim. think freelancer in 2d
very detailed and fun space rpg

Complex, challenging and rewarding. a full fledge gaming experience on your Android device. Only thing that could be better is he ability of cloud cross platform save games. Trese brothers may be a little indie developer studio, but that dont cease to amaze me
Trese Brothers games are a shining example of what mobile games should be. This is their best one yet.
This game is wonderfully done, with an amazing amount of depth. The developers are responsive and update often. Worth every penny, and more. Great job!
Awesome! I love it. Worth every penny and then some.
This game is fantastic and totally my style. lots of customization, engaging story, and I can be a space pirate. I didn't know there were games this good for mobile.
Hecking awesome

great game. my greatest criticism is that THERE'S NO GODDAMN TUTORIAL. Once you've probably blundered and had your first ship die horribly, the second ship gets way easier since you know what you're doing

By far the best phone game I'be ever played, very in depth and feels like your getting a well thought out full indie game rather than the usual cash grab Gacha games with cheap clickbait. Definitely worth every penny.
replyContent: I am sorry to hear you are having problems with your device. If you email me at cory.trese@gmail.com I will try to help -- and if your device is no longer supported by Google or Google Play, I will help you get a refund. Thanks!

content: best devs on the market. great game.
Great game! Definitely worth it.
Legitimately one of the best games I've played on Android. If space simulation and political intrigue is your thing, it's well worth the purchase price.
No cloud save.
Great sequel to the original Star Traders
Great stuff again from these guys.

The design is simply too cluttered and opaque. I can never tell how anything is supposed to work, or how I can even get to do the actual merchanting part of the game. I've been a diehard fan of the original for many years, but this one just seems like overcomplicated nonsense :/
replyContent: I will definitely consider your opinion and try to make the game better. Please email us any specific suggestions at cory.trese@gmail.com.

content: so long as they re-balance the xeno in ground combat then I am all for this game been here since the beginning even back as far as the first star traders game. so by the gods please fix the bugs and balance the xenos in ground combat please and thank you.
replyContent:
Hello,
We are sorry that you do not like the game but we thank you for your feedback. Our future updates will try to improve the game. Feel free to email me at cory.trese@gmail.com if you need further support or Xeno killing tips.

content: Interestingly complex and fun game but like others have mentioned the reputation system is retarded and anti-fun. Being penaltized for pretty much anything you do is tremendously stupid, e.g: almost everyship encounter will make you loose rep even if you're a law abiding bounty hunter wanting to leave merchants/explorers alone.

Ok. Now I have my money back, I will give middling rating. I have been online gaming for more than 6 years and understand most games. Found this game difficult to follow. Obviously requires different mindset. Just not my cup of tea.
it's really boring. I see where some people can find enjoyment, but I can't.

everything is good now! if you email them they actually respond. i have no more complaints except that you should allow a optional feature to turn the user interface green like Fallout. blue and white are the hardest colors to see if youre visually impaired as it bleeds together. so to have the text green&black would really help me! i have 14 eye conditions:[
replyContent: We'd love to understand what went wrong with your game. Please email us at cory.trese@gmail.com so that we can try to fix it for you.

content: I'm honestly struggling to find a fault with this game. Interesting, deeply mechanical gameplay?: Check. A story with player choice and involvement?: Check Nice soundtrack?: Check Multiple ships, classes and ways to play?: Check. These are the sort of refreshing games we need on mobile platforms. I haven't had that much fun with a mobile title for a while. I do have to point out I am still in the early-mid game so don't know how things turn out later on. For now however, heavily recommended!
5/5â˜† Top notch as always!
love it !!!

Trese Brothers are in a totally different class compared to other mobile developers. Their games are deeper than most PC games and yet you can play them on your phone. Play this game all the time on PC and the previous game Star Traders RPG was a favorite of mine since long before that. Cant reccomend this game enough. If you like the idea of a space captain simulator with lots of intrigue and a setting like a mix of 40k and Dune, you'll love this game.
Very good game, but not easy to learn. well need to put in some effort reading before you can really enjoy it, so don't expect a casual game at first.

Love the game. It scratches that rogue like itch for me. First was frustrated that I could not survive longer than 2 years but the more I played and learned the longer I survived and more of the game opened up. 10/10 would recommend. The only annoying thing is that half of the unlocks are "comming soon" which means if the game gonna get abandoned by the devs we will never see them.

What a fantastic game... Deep, still evolving tactics, strategy and story elements. This isn't a shallow, 15 minute experience. This is a full ship and crew RPG set in an open sandbox universe. The map manages to feel alive, and the more story elements the Dev adds the more engaging the game is. Meaningful achievement unlocks creates a powerful motivation to improve. One of my favorite games on any platform. Fair warning, you're going to fail hard before you get things figured out.
One of the greatest mobile games of all time.
Amazing game. Especially for the price. Buy this thing.
Best Game!!!
Seriously, you don't own this game yet? Thanks for turning my phone into a gaming system again.

For the first time, my usual complaint with their games doesn't stick out: the music seems less annoyingly repetitive than in previous games. =D The game is large and provides plenty to do, the only immediate gripes I have is that I can't compare crew equipment to what I have available before buying, I'd like to easily see how well/badly my crew is doing when taking damage in ship combat, and the game should NOTIFY IN A POPUP about deaths of crewmembers... Name and profession, please. ^^

I love this game so far. It's hard, but it's super fun! My only complaint right now is a glitch where after I loaded a past save file, all my character graphica disappeared and were replaces by shadow outlines. That's a bummer, as now I can't see anyone's faces, clothes, or weapons, which are all very well desogned. Hoping an update will fix this.

An absolutely fantastic upgrade from the original. As a player heavily focused on piracy and combat, the original lacked a lot to keep me engaged, though I still purchased it and the options, and enjoyed to a point. Been out of the loop for a few years with my gaming, but by random chance ManTheMaker's channel popped up on my recommended feed and showcased this game. Snagged it immediately and couldn't be more pleased with the game and the designers. Trese Bro's are legit as it gets.

After learning how the game works, which took me about an hour, I found that there weren't any interesting upgrades for my ship! All the weapons are the same few with different re-skins. Runs stable and is fun. There's just not much below the surface.
Awesome very expansive fu_&-(king space travel event spawn is shotty something happens every 5sec. Also the crew whines likes B_&$+($ my only whiney bitxch complaint.

Trese Brothers knock another one out of the park. As deep as NMS was/is shallow, and seems daunting (I love it!). UI can be slightly cramped on phones, but otherwise perfect. Not a single crash yet, but occasionally the character models will not load after backgrounding the app, closing and reopening fixes the issue.
replyContent: Thanks for letting me know about the character models. This might be a memory issue in the Android port on the Galaxy S7. I will investigate and try to come up with a patch. Thanks for letting me know!

content: Thanks to the great community Trese Brothers have founded, to the members of the community to back these wonderful games, and to the hard work the community and brothers do to develop these awesome games. While also continuing updating their other much loved games in their library. Congratulations to everyone.
Great game.

Played the original star traders a ton, so I was super excited when this was released, purchased almost instantly. However, the crew combat sequences really bother me, and I'm not even entirely sure why. it's almost like they feel too slow, and take me out of the immersion. it's difficult to pinpoint, but it's probably just preference. Amazing Space Simulator and much more!  This is a difficult game to properly describe, but it's a Space Trade Exploration Adventure RPG with Global Events triggering things throughout the galaxy. That being said, it can also be played as a sandbox game.  Choose your primary Career, your Faction affiliation, select your initial skill and attributes, hire and train your crew, purchase and upgrade your ship, promote your best crew to Officers, and launch yourself into the void of space.Â   Whether you play as a merchant, pirate, spy, explorer, military commander (or several other careers), you'll be challenged by faction wars, trade bans, offers of missions to faraway sectors with great risk/reward, hostile ship attacks, and the ever-present risk of Xeno attacks in space or wilderness zones.  The contacts you meet will offer missions to enhance your reputation with factions (or turn you into a war criminal with other factions). Many of the missions lead to story arcs in which you can help shape major events and shake up the galaxy.  The decisions are yours Captain. You are a Star Trader. Definite Buy! EDIT: Salvaging abandoned ships and fighter craft launchers bring a whole new level!

Absolutely outstanding. Everything good about the original star traders plus better graphics, music, and sound.   Story lines have been added with developed NPCs and plotlines.  A great improvement on the original star traders in terms of gameplay mechanics as well, especially since escaping from the dreaded xeno is far easier.   The major weakness of the game is the complexity.  This isn't a beer and pretzels game and there is a largish amount of detail. I confess to almost turning off the game when I saw that I had to keep track of 30+ individual crew, with their own traits and skills and necessary training.     If you want to enjoy this, you're going to need to spend some serious time with it.  Even with this, though, it's a great ride if you're willing to put the time in to appreciate it.

Really great game, exceeded my expectations. I've always loved the Trese brother games, but this one has a level of polish and shine that I've never seen in their games before. Imagine if elite, darkest dungeon, and FTL were mushed together, that's what this game feels like.

these guys.... i would buy ANY console just to play one of their games. i love these motherfu***rs. they seriously make the only mobile games WORTH PLAYING. look.... if you have 6 dollars and are looking for a steal of a deal PLEASE support these developers, it can only get better from here ladies and gents.

content: Very solid gameplay and game mechanics. The scope and depth was a bit over overwhelming at first, but it didn't take me long to pick up. I only wish there is cloud save so I can play my character on multiple devices.

content: Wonderful game with responsive developers. The only word of caution I could give other players is that, while I was fine on a Pixel 3 XL, I could see the controls being difficult on a smaller screen.

1. Had to uninstall it to get the sound to stop; not even closing it works. 2. Tutorial is almost non-existent, and saving doesn't help due to what seems to be an autosave overwrite. In other words, there's no way to fix it when you think you're doing one thing, but you're actually doing something else. 3. Too easy to screw up, esp. with a touchpad; for example, I wasn't even ready to leave the planet, but all of a sudden I was zipping off to empty space. If you could at least autosave and autoload TO THE EXACT POINT AND STATE THAT YOU SAVED, it looks like it could be at least three to four stars. Combine that with permadeath, and a stray touch leading to permadeath, and this is a loser as is; add to that the price of seven bucks... grr. The biggest killer is the contrast with what looks to be a really cool game, with much replay and depth, and the points above and it adds up to a really aggravating disappointment. Add: it mostly likely _is_ an issue with chromebook, most particularly the touchpad; I've had issues there regarding cursor jump and multi-touch with other apps, though not to this degree. I won't be requesting a refund, as TB is a solid producer of great, bang-for-bucks, products. TL; DR - I hated it because I can't play it confidently, not because it's a bad game for everyone.
replyContent: We were able to fix the sound bug in the last update, so hope you'll take another look!

content: ever wanted to command your own ship and crew? this is it

Space exploration, trading, battling and diplomacy? I was sold the moment i saw this game. I didn't know it before I heard about it on /r/androidgaming and am I glad it was trending there! The gameplay is deep, complex and you have to pay attention on your actions since mistakes will be pretty damaging. The tutorial is lacking but after a couple hous you'll get the hang of it. It is played offline and the battery impact is pretty low on my LG G3 F400 (about 3 hours of gameplay per charge). I really can't recommend this game enough!

it's an great game. I've always been a big fan of star traders games since my first Android phone. the atmosphere and universe is great. Be aware, you will die and you will lose an ungodly amount of time on this game :)
#1 Top Paid for a reason. Long-awaited and delivers. Enjoying the new features and updates!
a great big black hole of time. pick it up and lose hours at a time. fantastic game with great depth to keep you coming back. another fab game from the trese brothers. thanks.

content: Not a fan of the excessive random events that hemorrhage money and kill the immersion for me. I took a 16 jump mission that paid 80K and completed it. content: Working really well on a 10" tablet. Fantastic job with the port.

replyContent: We are working on a UI scaling setting and investigating a cloud service. We hear you!

content: What a game! This is a PC game released on mobile - it's deep, satisfying, challenging, interesting and absolutely addicting. Prepare to 'just play for 2 minutes' and find out you've been spending 40 minutes on your phone. Buy it.
Lots of replayability, best game that the Trese Brothers have come out with

Starship captain simulator sandbox with huge freedom as well as solid stories. Bounty hunting, trading (legal and illegal), military officer, spying, exploring, diplomat are all viable specialisations. You can do whatever so long as you can pay your crew and the fuel/repair bills. The game is complicated and doesn't hold your hand explaining systems. Play a game on Basic to figure out how stuff works before playing on a challenging setting as it can be hardcore. Best game on android.
High Quality. 10/10. Game is alot of fun. Kind of difficult but fair if you plan ahead.

Excellent, as always. I've been a Patreon patron of the Trese brothers for a while and not regretted a penny. These are consistently made sandbox games with real replayability. STF extends the Star Traders universe with an almost infinite amount of ways of playing. Give it a go - turn based strategy and RPG in one elegant package.
So far the port seems pretty good. Ui is a bit cluttered but that can't be avoided. Good job guys!
replyContent:
We will keep working on improvements and trying to streamline the UI. Thank you very much for playing.
